snippet.textDisplay: It seems that the makers of the film are trying to be clever by using the name Siren as some kind of Easter egg , but siren is an actual English synonym for mermaid. Sirena is the word for mermaid in Italian, Spanish, and Catalan, and possibly other languages. Many other languages use very similar variations, too. US people think they’re so clever yet don’t know basic common knowledge. They are the ones using a different word for something almost everyone else agrees on, and then because they don’t know this end up using the common word while assuming their own esoteric superiority. How unironic.
